the art of computer programming donald e knuth arts at stanford university presented by sica home search this site arts enews subscribe featured archive gallery the art of computer programming donald e knuth an inside look at the man behind the art of computer programming his inspirations motivations and passion for creativity professor knuth is the author of the seminal multi volume the art of computer programming the father of the analysis of algorithms and the writer of countless computer programs several of which have over a million users he is also a creative writer a musician and an artist during his long career as a computer programmer knuth has worked with artists from many different disciplines including design typography and calligraphy these collaborations resulted in innovative projects like tex which revolutionized digital typesetting in the early 1980s and is still widely used today professor knuth's website home calendar gallery news visiting artists grants organizations facilities plan a visit about sica students faculty staff make a gift volunteer login press sitemap contact connect twitter facebook vimeo flickr 2011 stanford university all rights reserved local user login
